  "prompt": "What's a psychosis?",
  "response": "Psychosis is a mental health condition characterized by a disconnection from reality. People experiencing psychosis may:\n\n1. Have hallucinations (seeing, hearing, or feeling things that aren't real)\n2. Experience delusions (false beliefs that aren't based in reality)\n3. Have disorganized thinking and speech\n4. Exhibit unusual or erratic behavior\n\nPsychosis can be caused by various factors, including:\n- Mental health disorders like schizophrenia\n- Bipolar disorder\n- Severe depression\n- Drug use\n- Brain injuries\n- Neurological conditions\n- Extreme stress\n\nTreatment typically involves:\n- Antipsychotic medications\n- Psychotherapy\n- Support from mental health professionals\n- Addressing underlying causes\n\nProfessional medical help is crucial for managing psychosis effectively.",
